According to the [[2020 United States census]], there were 1,258 people, 724 households, and 374 families residing in the town; the racial and ethnic composition of the town was 71.3% [[African Americans|Black and African American]], 25.6% [[Non-Hispanic whites|non-Hispanic white]], 0.24% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.08% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2.31% [[Multiracial people|multiracial]] or of another race/ethnicity, and 0.48% [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race in 2020.<ref name=":0" /> According to the 2020 [[American Community Survey]], its median household income was $30,682.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2020 Income Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Centreville+town,+Mississippi+income&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1901 |access-date=November 26, 2022 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

